Access modifier
methods and variables can be:
1. public- accecable everywhere
2. default -  given by default, when key words are not given.
            its only accecable within the same package... class in Day29 cannot call default from day30 class
3. private- access to the class is very limited, cannot be used outside the class
4. protected


Top level classs can hold two access modifiers:public and default



PUBLIC:
to call public from a different package:  Import -> packageName.->className
    int defaultAccess =1000;//default
    public int publicAccess=2000;//public

PRIVATE:
only accessable in the same class
private long SSN - you can only use this ssn variable inside of this class.
                - cannot be accessed even if in the same package, but different classes
